{
  "text": "Consistent with Eq. (16), only one atom of the pair is rotated during the integration, with L being the normalisation factor [cf. Eq. (19)]. The pairwise integrals in [CITATION_1] are calculated in two steps. We first define R ij to be the rotation matrix which aligns r j onto r i , and then perform the change of variableR = RR T ij (and analogouslỹ",
